    <p>ZURICH • Fifa will trial con­cus­sion sub­sti­tutes at the Feb 1-11 Club World Cup in Qatar, football’s world gov­ern­ing body said yes­ter­day.</p>
    <p>The de­ci­sion comes af­ter the game’s rule-mak­ing body Ifab gave the go-ahead to ad­di­tional tri­als last month. The trial will al­low one per­ma­nent con­cus­sion re­place­ment in cases of head in­jury, re­gard­less of the num­ber of sub­sti­tu­tions a team has made.</p>


